description.narrative: UNICEF focused on facilitating strong and coordinated efforts among key ministries and duty-bearers to strengthen child protection systems and services for children who need care and protection, while at the same time supporting policy reforms and improving institutional capacity and skills of the duty bearers. The social service workforce under the Department of Social Services reached more than 200,000 children including 94,000 girls in 2021 with technical and financial support from UNICEF. More than 50 per cent received various direct services including psychosocial and family support, while the rest received referrals to specific services needed. | Status:Met | As-of Date:22/12/2021
